<item>
            <title>[LU-7487] NFS reply read: -13</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7487</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unsure if this the correct place to put this but none the less will try.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In short we host some Apache web sites from NFS mounts backed by Lustre and are having an issue where by a file gets uploaded to a directory and it is not readable by Apache and a return code of -13 appears to be returned. If I cp the file on the web server to a new location the web server can then read the file, assume the file hits the web server&apos;s cache and then works. Attached is an attempt to trace the various layers from Apache down to the Lustre client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If someone has the time perhaps they can have a look as any insight would be appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; &lt;br/&gt;
Eric Kolb&lt;br/&gt;
DCS - UVic Systems&lt;br/&gt;
University of Victoria&lt;br/&gt;
Office: 250-721-7658&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Apache running over NFS&lt;br/&gt;
RHEL 5/6 variants&lt;br/&gt;
Lustre re-exported via NFS Lustre 2.7.0 client&lt;br/&gt;
